HEADWORD: Muggletonian
<hw>Mug`gle*to"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>One of an extinct sect, named after <person>Ludovic
<etsep>Muggleton</etsep></person>, an English journeyman tailor, who
(about 1657) claimed to be inspired.</def> <rj><au>Eadie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

